BSE updates: 19 May 2000 2000.0832
Date: 22 Jun 2000
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Australian Broadcast Corp., 22 Jun 2000 [edited

BSE research update: Australia
--------------------------------
The Department of Primary Industries in Queensland is seeking nervous cows
acting strangely. Department veterinary officer Janet Berry says the cows
will be examined in a bid to prove Australia is free of the deadly mad cow
disease.
She is urging graziers to assist and says the late cattle mustering season
is a problem for researchers who require a quota of 25 sick cattle. The
researchers are looking for very specific neurological signs associated
with Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy. There are other diseases affecting
the neurological system, but the abnormal gaits and behaviours are what the
researchers are seeking.
--
